com.foreach.across.modules.entity.bind

Enum EntityPropertyBindingType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<EntityPropertyBindingType>
      • com.foreach.across.modules.entity.bind.EntityPropertyBindingType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<EntityPropertyBindingType>

    public enum EntityPropertyBindingType
extends Enum<EntityPropertyBindingType>
    Represents the type of property binder that should be used for a value. Usually a binding type is determined based on the property type, but in some cases it can be useful to specify it manually. For example if the property type is a custom implementation of a Map that should just be treated as a regular single value property.

    Note that is different from the EntityPropertyHandlingType, the latter determines if an EntityPropertiesBinder should be used, whereas the former determines how binding should be done if the EntityPropertiesBinder is used.

    Since:
    3.2.0
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme
    See Also:
    EntityPropertiesBinder

      • forProperty

        public static EntityPropertyBindingType forProperty(@NonNull
                                                    @NonNull EntityPropertyDescriptor descriptor)
        Resolve the binding type for a given property descriptor. If an attribute of type EntityPropertyBindingType.class is set, that value will be used. If not the property type (EntityPropertyDescriptor.getPropertyTypeDescriptor()) will be used to determine the binding type: by default a Collection will use COLLECTION and a Map will use MAP.
        Parameters:
        descriptor - to resolve the binding type for
        Returns:
        binding type - never null
